# The Synthetic Stress corpus is byte-exact by design: line endings, text
# encodings (UTF-16 + BOM), and decimal separators are part of what each file
# probes. Disable git's eol/encoding normalization so the exact bytes round-trip
# on every platform -- otherwise, e.g., the CRLF case would be normalized to LF
# and quietly stop testing CRLF handling.
*.csv  -text
*.txt  -text
*.ASC  -text
# expected-outcomes.md is normal prose -- leave it diffable (not listed here).
